  <div id="content">
    <section class="introduction">
<div>
<p>Our talented PPC team all have one thing in common. Mathematics
degrees. We reverse train mathematicians in search marketing
because that's the easy part of the job. The hard part is being
able to analyse and gain insights from terabytes of data.</p>
</div>
</section><div class="animation paid-search-1">
<img src="/img/animations/paid-search-1/paid-search-1.png" alt="" />
<span class="dial"><span class="needle"></span></span>
<span class="graph"></span>
</div><section><h3>Textbook PPC</h3><h4>delivering dramatic results</h4>
<p>Google recently described our approach to PPC as "text book".
Which explains why in most campaigns, we are able to deliver 30%
more conversions than our competitors for the same level of spend.
This is because we plan intelligently, thoroughly researching and
analysing your campaign and competitors before we start thinking
about bidding for ad space.</p>

<p>Our experts oversee a host of cutting edge bid management tools
as part of our Epiphany Fusion suite. We don't use any single tool
or proprietary system exclusively, meaning that we can innovate
quickly and respond to changes in the fast paced world of paid
search.</p>
</section><section><h3>Reports Designed For You</h3><h4>When you want them</h4>
<p>When you work with Epiphany you benefit from constant
innovation, attention to detail and useful reporting.</p>

<p>We are passionate about transparency, so we produce weekly and
monthly reports that are customised to your needs. We believe that
the data from your campaigns is yours, not ours, meaning that we're
accountable for every penny.</p>

<p>Our reports explain how your marketing funnel is working and
offer new ideas to maximise conversions and ROI. Our weekly
innovation meetings find new ways of improving paid search results,
testing new features to see if they offer value to you.</p>
</section><section><h3>International PPC Campaigns</h3><h4>Reach A Global Audience</h4>
<p>We are running paid search campaigns in over 30 territories.
Working closely with our partner Leeds Metropolitan University we
recruit linguists to help us make sure that our PPC ads convert in
every territory.</p>

<p>We concentrate on localisation over and above translation,
making sure that our campaigns account for local nuances, algorithm
variances and cultural contexts.</p>

<p>A quick look at our <a
href="/about/international-campaigns/">world map</a> shows our
world domination so far. We just need our intrepid search pioneers
to crack Greenland and Nepal frontier in the northern
hemisphere...</p>
</section><div class="animation paid-search-2">
<img src="/img/animations/paid-search-2/paid-search-2.png" alt="" />
<div class="bar-chart">
<span class="bar b1"></span>
<span class="bar b2"></span>
<span class="bar b3"></span>
<span class="bar b4"></span>
<span class="axis"></span>
</div>
<span class="pie-chart"></span>
<span class="gambling-report"></span>
</div><section><h3>Intelligent, Quality Ads</h3><h4>Pay Less, convert more</h4>
<p>We understand that successful paid search campaigns depend on a
joined up approach. That means that we work intelligently to
integrate all elements of your campaign.</p>

<p>Bringing together landing page relevance, ad performance,
keyword and advert relevance and geographic relevance improves your
ad's Quality Score. The higher your Quality Score, the lower the
price you pay per click meaning that we offer our clients the
benefit of paying less for a higher postion than their
competitors.</p>
</section><section><h3>Conversion Experts</h3><h4>Constant Testing &amp; Improvement</h4>
<p>How well your website converts visitors into enquiries or sales
is critical to the success of your business. Epiphany offer
WebConverter - a proven process, supported by a suite of cutting
edge technologies, that delivers incremental increases in
conversion rates by running a series of intelligent tests that give
greater insight into how users interact with your site.</p>

<p>As one of an elite group of&nbsp;<strong>Google Qualified
Conversion Professionals</strong>, we have on average helped our
clients increase their conversion rates by more than 28% over the
last twelve months.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
</section><section><h3>Expert Sector Analysis</h3><h4>Key Insights Make The Difference</h4>
<div>
<p>Our clients work in some of the most competitive sectors around.
We help make sense of the paid search landscape by regulary
producing in depth reports on search strategies, visibility and
keyword success. You can find our sector reports in our&nbsp;<a
href="/insights/industry-reports/" title="Industry Reports">library</a>.</p>

<p>Our indepth understanding of other brands' search strategies
means that we can help you formulate winning campaigns. Our insight
and understanding of your sector means that are in a unique
position to work closely with you as an integrated team.</p>

<br />
<div id="invisible"></div>
</div>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
</section><div class="animation paid-search-3">
<img src="/img/animations/paid-search-3/paid-search-3.png" alt="" />
<span class="bird-container">
<span class="bird"><span class="wing"></span></span>
</span>
</div><section><h3>Social Media PPC</h3><h4>The Power Of Networks</h4>
<p>We have been pioneering social advertising on Facebook since
2008 and also run&nbsp; social campaigns through Sponsored Tweets,
StumbleUpon and Digg! for many of our clients.</p>

<p>Social PPC regularly forms part of integrated SEO and PPC
strategies that are driven by remarkable content.</p>

<p>We understand that the future of search marketing is social and
our team of talented analysts, copywriters and designers are all
experts in this fast changing but crucial factor.</p>
</section><section><h3>Mobile And Tablets</h3><h4>Move With Your Customers</h4>
<p>Over 50% of new internet connections already come from mobile
devices so we include mobile phone PPC analysis in every campaign
we run. Consumers are using an ever increasing range of devices to
go online, indeed mobile accounted for 12% of paid search clicks
leading up to Christmas 2011. Yet mobile only accounted 7.5% of
search spend, meaning that mobile advertisers secure less expensive
clicks.</p>

<p>We analyse mobiles and tablets in the same way as we interrogate
desktop searches. Our copywriters, web developers and conversion
rate specialists understand what it takes to run successful mobile
paid search.</p>
</section><section><h3>PPC Phone Tracking</h3><h4>Get Greater Insight</h4>
<p>We know that people want different things and behave differently
when searching on desktop, tablet and mobile, which means that we
operate systems that allow our clients to track mobile traffic and
campaigns seperately.</p>

<p>We can track who is clicking through from mobile or tablets,
what devices they have and what actions they are taking on your
landing page. We optimise your pages for mobile and tablet
visitors. This means that our PPC campaigns work as hard on mobiles
and tablets as they do on a desktop.</p>
</section><img src="/img/animations/paid_search_4.png" alt="" class="animation" /><section><h3>Yahoo!, Baidu And Microsoft</h3><h4>Paid Search Beyond Google</h4>
<p>Google accounts for the majority of traffic in most territories
but our search marketing specialists are also experienced in
running campaigns through other networks when it could give you
better results.</p>

<p>We've succesfully managed international campaigns through Yahoo!
Search Marketing, Microsoft Ad Centre, Yandex and Baidu in many of
our international and domestic paid search campaigns.</p>
</section>
